## Overview

The RCSB PDB Pipeline discovers protein structures in the Protein Data Bank that
correspond to a set of input proteins (identified by UniProt accession), fetches
their complete structural metadata from the official RCSB Data API, enhances it
with UniProt annotations (sequence, GO terms, names, taxonomy), then produces a
deduplicated, sanitized, ML-ready dataset.

### What it solves

| Problem | Solution |
|---------|----------|
| UniProt IDs don't directly map to PDB entries | Uses RCSB Search API to find all PDB entries per UniProt |
| RCSB GraphQL schema has 317 types, 2398 fields — overwhelming | Schema explorer + preset field selection |
| Raw API responses have duplicates, nulls, inconsistent types | Full sanitization pipeline with configurable strategies |
| Need different output shapes for different ML tasks | Multiple granularity modes + aggregation strategies |
| Team needs reproducible, auditable datasets | Checkpoint system + full run reports + config snapshots |

